# UX #2: romm-run's reserved Wi-Fi-down code (102) maps to the Wi-Fi copy + the #3
# expectation line; the wrapper no longer collides with engine exit codes.
desc fetch hook: wrapper rc=102 (Wi-Fi down) -> Wi-Fi copy + expectation line, stub intact
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
sdfile Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
engine 102|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace SHOW2 simple text='Wi-Fi not connected — enable it in NextUI Settings. The game screen that follows will fail to open — that's expected. Fix the connection and launch again.'
expect_file_empty Roms/Game Boy Advance (GBA)/✘ Zelda.gba
